description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you an experienced Human Resources, Organisational Development or Learning and Development &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;professional, with experience in appraisals and supervision? We have an exciting opportunity to join our Leadership and Management Development Team within our Education Department on a 12month fixed-term contract.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;As the Appraisal Lead, you will run a project designed to review and implement an appraisal and &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;supervision system across Surrey and Borders Partnership NHS Foundation Trust. You will have experience of running projects, the ability to involve a wide variety of stakeholders and gain their engagement and be able to design, implement, train and evaluate a new appraisal and supervision system. Essential to this role will be working in partnership and working collaboratively with operational leaders and key departments to develop engagement and commitment to the new system.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be enthusiastic, self-motivated and have excellent influencing skills, with a drive to deliver to challenging timescales. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working hours: 37.5 hours per week, Monday to Friday&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information please contact: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Alison.newport@sabp.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
